dhwZEztw","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"TSH elevada y T4 libre baja","guid":"WheWka11iUUZg3kpencQMA","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"83","text":"Hipotiroidismo\\Nsubclínico","guid":"0WeBhwjtI71rXOu0j0gVBw","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"TSH ligeramente elevada, T4 libre normal\\Ny T3 libre normal","guid":"afw6Lt6XurrlxmlQSYPr-Q","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"Si \\N(Recomendación fuerte)","guid":"_1YYplPgz6HfvRQQrXngKQ","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"TSH ≥10","guid":"jhb5i4pLcrJfzRRdU78pCw","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"Especialmente\\Ncon antiTPO","guid":"v0mmNXqlRZT0o_waGjH35A","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"86","text":"Embarazadas o que planean un embarazo\\N(recomendación de baja)","guid":"ol0SC-A-0VyQ8EchYY-3xg","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"Historial actual o\\Npasado de antiTPO","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"82","text":"Dosis","guid":"p49GWDziRgg3obM4Igo9zQ","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Hipotiroidismo\\Nmanifiesto","guid":"IU8TuSm064zRry6PWeebTg","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"Considere comenzar con una dosis de reemplazo\\Ncompleta de 1,6 mcg/kg/día (100-125 mcg/día)","guid":"xaGdfIAjGwGJs2mHhcB0dw","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"94","text":"Considere las dosis iniciales más bajas (12,5-50 mcg/día) para pacientes\\Nmayores de 50 años o con enfermedad arterial coronaria concomitante","guid":"W5CyfON6SD8_sPmpppH5Nw","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"94","text":"En las mujeres embarazadas, aumente la dosis de levotiroxina entre un\\N25 % y un 30 % tan pronto como se conozca el embarazo\\N(recomendación fuerte).","guid":"_Pr_a-qinNXZDB7-J63rPQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"93","text":"Hipotiroidismo\\Nsubclínico","guid":"DDZ7pQ_Bb_0ZENUepTPRuQ","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"Levotiroxina 25-75 mcg/día, dependiendo\\Ndel grado de elevación de la TSH","guid":"XnV6HaOutP6DmqPIroP5Dw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"0","text":"Seguimiento","guid":"4RH8wESoMYGPVoVfcsxH3Q","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"Controle los\\Nniveles de TSH","guid":"lqIOhYrvz3xXKeng1HPz4g","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"4-6 semanas después de iniciar el tratamiento, cambiar la dosis o iniciar otros\\Nmedicamentos que cambian la biodisponibilidad o el metabolismo de la levotiroxina","guid":"BHvvTgiM7cz9RrlPqsHJPQ","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"Luego 6 meses después de la dosis estable alcanzada, luego cada 12 meses\\N(recomendación fuerte).","guid":"zOUtbhS75gzqdoMtDPQwsw","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"100","text":"No controle los niveles de anticuerpos\\Nporque no se reducen con levotiroxina.","guid":"4O7JeGLtfZpEDxuH9o_0Zw","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"100","text":"En los pacientes que no reciben tratamiento, controle los niveles de TSH al inicio,\\N6 meses y luego cada 1-2 años o para detectar nuevos síntomas de hipotiroidismo.","guid":"XiEcfqjzAA0dsXSwpWZr8Q","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":105,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas","filename":"- Tiroiditis de Hashimoto","id":"map_105","resolved_references":[]}